title.24: Doctor Strange & Doctor Doom: Triumph and Torment (1989)
title.66: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #5

description.0: BARON MORDO STRIKES! Strange's most persistent nemesis has a new trick up his sleeve -- and it just might cost Strange his soul!
description.2: While on the road, Murdock stops at a Bed & Breakfast for the night. What began as an overnight visit, leads to DD helping the B&B owner out of a sticky legal jam!
description.3: Excalibur thwarts the plans of their evil doppelg'ngers from Earth-597, while Kitty and Alistaire Stuart explore their chemistry.
description.4: The Hulk takes on the Necrophage in Hell!
description.5: Tony Stark facing dangers from the past and present! Find out what Marvel has in store for the Iron Avenger in this Giant-sized Special!
description.8: Annihilus charges his way to Asgard, where he confronts Odin himself! It's a clash of kings as the lord of the Negative Zone faces off with the lord of Asgard!
description.10: Trolls have captured X-Factor. Will there be a fairy tale ending of an escape for the mutant team?
description.12: FRIGHTFUL FOUR VS. FANTASTIC FOUR! After suffering a defeat by the Frightful Four, Ben Grimm must fight the voices in his head in order to save the other members of the Fantastic Four and take the Frightful Four prisoner.
description.13: Still stationed in Australia, the X-Men take leave from service to tie up some loose ends. Dazzler gets a peek into her future. Wolverine encounters old friends...and foes. Plus, is Senator Kelly's wife in grave danger?
description.17: What if the Avengers had lost the Evolutionary War? Peer into a reality where Earth's Mightiest were defeated by the High Evolutionary. When the High Evolutionary sets off a mutation bomb that affects all of humankind and mutantkind, what will happen when an entire world is super-powered?
description.18: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #129. ""Paper, Not Paper."" Thirteen-year-old Kitty Pryde falls into a fantastical storybook where she's tempted by Emma Frost to reject the X-Men.
description.19: An African poaching ring has been killing dinosaurs, but their operation ends here...at the end of Wolverine's claws and Punisher's firearms! That is, if Wolverine and Punisher don't kill each other first.
description.20: Spider-Man vs. Venom...at Aunt May's house! And in this case, Spidey doesn't have the home turf advantage. Spider-Man may not be able to defeat Eddie Brock, but can he take out his alien symbiote instead?
description.21: The Avengers Hydrobase gets attacked by a horde of lava men! Will the Avengers be able to stop the infiltration when the odds are stacked against them?
description.22: Can the Living Legend survive the most startling transformation of all? Steve Rogers--a kid again! Plus: Battle Star meets the Falcon!
description.26: Hawkeye is in danger of becoming plant food at the green-thumbed hands of Plantman!  Plus, more mind-bending action from Moondragon!
description.29: The Bushman has captured the woman Moon Knight loves! To help save her life, Moon Knight must get help from Spider-Man!
description.32: A macabre tale of high-seas piracy, death, and justice!
description.33: Katie Power learns the true origins behind the Power Pack costumes in this whacky interdimensional adventure!
description.36: A series of experiments to cure world hunger leads to some disturbing discoveries that Speedball must clean up.
description.38: Matt Murdock is in a desperate state. Reeling from his break-up with Karen, and fighting his own murderous impulses, it may be best to leave town. Murdock does just that, but before he goes, DD must save a young boy from a group of thugs!
description.39: Excalibur comes face-to-face with Lightning Force! Can the team take down their own doppelgangers...with Captain Britain and Meggan's powers slowly dwindling?
description.40: The Hulk takes a stroll through the streets of Vegas, looking for some trouble...
description.41: Tony Stark is rushed to the hospital after being shot by stalker Kathy Dare. The bullet has ruptured his spine and he has lost consciousness. Will America's favorite playboy survive the latest attempt on his life?
description.44: Thor and The Warriors Three follow a trail of blood-curdling screams to discover cocoons filled with dead Asgardians...drained to fuel the peerless power of Annihilus!
description.46: These Trolls aren't the cute kind with the bad hair. These are the Trolls who are angry and powerful and they have kidnapped Alchemy! X-Factor must race to the rescue!
description.48: The FF must form an unlikely alliance - with Kang the Conqueror! But can even their combined strength stop the evil plot of the dark sorceror Necrodamus?
description.49: On a guys' night out in the Australian outback, Wolverine and fellow X-Men, Longshot, Havok and Colossus, encounter an interstellar group of conquerors known simply as The Conquest. Will the X-Men be able to curb this trouble before locals are endangered?
description.52: It’s a big universe out there, and not everyone’s received the news that the Silver Surfer is no longer Galactus’s herald! In fact, some planets have been making plans to kill the Surfer in order to save their planet from Galactus. And the Surfer’s about to discover how effective those plans are!
description.54: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #128. ""Double Negative."" The Hellfire Club's White Queen teaches a servant a lesson in control and domination.
description.55: Wolverine guest-stars! The Punisher and Wolverine are trailing the same poaching ring in Africa- why then are these two fighting each other? With their hair-trigger tempers, this unlikely team-up may be more cause for concern than cause for good!
description.56: Death's Head and youthful protégé Spratt are on the hunt for Photofit, a shapeshifter, who's chosen to hide in plain sight in a TV studio!
description.60: Venom's back and ready to tear Spider-Man a new one! But why does Venom hate Spidey so much? With Todd McFarlane on pencils the real question is: Who cares?
description.61: The Avengers encounter Puma, a genetically engineered Native American who is tracking a mutant from his own tribe. The young mutant in question, Charles Little Sky, accidentally opens a dimensional rift which frees the U-Foes from exile.
description.62: Captain America takes on the Red Skull's merciless minion, the Taskmaster!
description.65: Marc Spector's first adventure brings him face to face with the man who caused him to become Moon Knight -- Bushman!
description.69: When a trader's caravan wanders into the Lost Valley of Forgotten Beasts, can even Conan save them from the prehistoric jaws of death?
description.70: Can Hawkeye escape a garden of death run by the deadly Plantman!  Plus, Black Panther springs into solo action!
description.72: The Star Child has grown at last, and comes to a startling revelation about himself, and his relation to both Ken Connell and the mysterious Old Man! But how does Jacob Burnley factor into this new truth?
description.73: The trial of Joe Robertson starts here! Can Peter manage both heavy courtroom drama and a gang war between Kingpin and the Lobo Brothers?
description.74: Robbie’s parents reveal their past connection to Alex Bow, causing a lot of heartache for Speedball.
description.75: A duel with a deadly dragon, alongside the descendants of King Arthur and his knights? Just another day defending the world as the Sorcerer Supreme!
description.78: Daredevil drinks alone on Christmas Eve. Fellow patrons at the bar share tales of loneliness, heartbreak, and regret. A seductive barfly isn't what she seems. Ann Nocenti's Daredevil at its best- dream-like, dizzying, and positively stunning!
description.79: Excalibur decides to stay in New York for a few days. Tensions run high between Captain Britain and Meggan- will the two set aside their pride? Kitty meets the New Mutants at the former X-Mansion...
description.80: The Hulk has been trapped in a fantasy world where everything he imagines becomes real! Can Bruce Banner convince his alter ego to snap out of it?
description.81: The Mandarin challenges Tony Stark to a winner takes all match! If he wins, Stark Enterprises is free to open up shop in Hong Kong. But if he loses, the Iron Avenger must work exclusively for the Mandarin - forever!
description.84: The first diabolical duo that ever menaced the Thunder God is back! The Executioner and the Enchantress have returned to Midgard, and they want Thor's head on a platter! But who is this new Executioner?
description.88: MR. FANTASTIC AND INVISIBLE WOMAN ARE BACK IN ACTION! And not a moment too soon, as the FF must deal with the aftermath of The Frightful Four's attack on Four Freedoms Plaza.
description.89: Introducing Jubilee! A young mutant teenager is creating her own fireworks in an L.A mall for money. But her burgeoning abilities have attracted the attention of a few unhappy patrons, among them mutant hunters! Will a few X-Men on a shopping spree be able to save the young Jubilee? The introduction to one of Marvel's most beloved mutants!
description.91: The Silver Surfer must make one of the most anguishing moral choices of his life on an alien planet about to be annihilated by a dragon!
description.92: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #127. ""So Good It Hurts."" Havok deals with traumatic hallucinations while driving with his girlfriend Polaris. On their way to assist the X-Men, Havok realizes that a civilian life is what he truly wants.
description.96: Hawkeye is in the eye of the storm as he throws down with Twister!  Plus, a mind-bending adventure with Moondragon!

0.text: BARON MORDO STRIKES! Strange's most persistent nemesis has a new trick up his sleeve -- and it just might cost Strange his soul!

1.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 12: Voices Heard, Voices Ignored. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 12: Zanti Chikane returns to the solar glider to help T’Challa recover from his wounds.

6.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 11: The Official Version. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 11: Anton Pretorius and his Minister of Security appear on TV to issue a warning about the Black Panther, still at large!

7.text: Brightwind flies once more! And that means Dani Moonstar, Mirage, must rise as a Valkyrie against Hel!

14.text: A tale from Wolverine's Department H days! A mercenary group learns their sins are catching up with them, and so is a guy with claws!

16.text: Silver Surfer is tricked into becoming an ally of the Skrulls in their battle against the Badoons and Kree.

23.text: A new set of uniforms and a new sales scheme threaten to destroy the whole Damage Control operation- and Iron Man!

24.text: Doctor Doom and Doctor Strange enter Mephisto's realm in an all-out effort to free the soul of Doctor Doom's mother! But what price must be paid before Mephisto will release it? And will Doctor Doom make the sacrifice?

25.text: Namor’s saga continues amidst Marvel’s mutants! Remember when the Sub-Mariner was a member of Magneto's Brotherhood of Evil Mutants? In case you don’t, we’ve got you covered! Daredevil guest-stars!

27.text: When Mysterio comes to start trouble, Spider-Man usually follows! In this special issue we see Spidey and She-Hulk join arms to take on the Headmen!

28.text: Will the Morituri's seizure of power mean worldwide stability or global civil war?

30.text: The Punisher enters the ring to knock out a corrupt promoter who’s looking to cash in on an unsuspecting boxer.

31.text: It’s the fateful final issue! Wolfpack battles in the Bedlam Corp Headquarters in a drag-out melee that will leave you reeling!

36.text: A series of experiments to cure world hunger leads to some disturbing discoveries that Speedball must clean up.

37.text: Contain’s only Panther’s Quest Part 10: Personal Risk. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 10: T’Challa tries to elude the capture of the South African security forces.

42.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 9: Justifiable Action. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 9: T’Challa must overcome a gunshot wound to fight the driver of the truck responsible for the tear gas attack, but more soldiers are on the way.

43.text: The mansion-less New Mutants go nautical with the X-Terminators!

50.text: The Hulk's having a bad day, and that means NO ONE'S having a good one! No one except Wolverine!

52.text: It’s a big universe out there, and not everyone’s received the news that the Silver Surfer is no longer Galactus’s herald! In fact, some planets have been making plans to kill the Surfer in order to save their planet from Galactus. And the Surfer’s about to discover how effective those plans are!

53.text: Doctor Doom enters the fray in this issue…and Iron Man’s feeling not so ‘superior’!

57.text: Behold! A new incarnation of the Vision is born. How will this new Vision differ from his old self? And will his heightened powers prove too threatening for even his teammates?

58.text: Damage Control’s Accountants vs. Doctor Doom! An untraditional smackdown featuring bureaucracy, debt, and financial restitution. Who’s' going to collect? The Fantastic Four guest-star.

59.text: The Avengers get a taste of Marvel's mightiest malcontents: The Hulk and the Sub-Mariner!

60.text: Venom's back and ready to tear Spider-Man a new one!  But why does Venom hate Spidey so much?  With Todd McFarlane on pencils the real question is: Who cares?

63.text: Mysterio, usually one of Spider-Man's greatest foes, curiously aims to cast his illusions onto She-Hulk now! Who or what is behind all of this?

64.text: The Earth's government is in disarray. The Morituri are in total disgrace. A coup d'etat is moments away.

66.text: Cloak is presumed dead, and Dagger must decide who will take over the mantle and his Cloak of Darkness!

67.text: Punisher ushers in more sin in ‘Sin City’! And the Vegas strip will never be the same by the time Frank’s finished!

68.text: With one member dead, an unlikely friend of the Wolfpack steps in to help defeat their greatest enemy yet…The Masterminds!

71.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 8: Hatred under Tears. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 8: T’Challa tries to disable a truck that is attacking the people of the township with tear gas.

72.text: The Star Child has grown at last, and comes to a startling revelation about himself, and his relation to both Ken Connell and the mysterious Old Man! But how does Jacob Burnley factor into this new truth?

73.text: The trial of Joe Robertson starts here! Can Peter manage both heavy courtroom drama and a gang war between Kingpin and the Lobo Brothers?

74.text: Robbie’s parents reveal their past connection to Alex Bow, causing a lot of heartache for Speedball.

75.text: A duel with a deadly dragon, alongside the descendants of King Arthur and his knights? Just another day defending the world as the Sorcerer Supreme!

77.text: Contains Panther’s Quest Part 7: Battered Artifacts and Damage Control in 'Overture'. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 7: T’Challa and Zanti Chikane confront Patrick Slade once and for all!

82.text: Contains Panther’s Quest Part 6: Naked Exposures & She-Hulk in 'X-Mas Tease'. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 6: The South African Magistrate of Communications, Anton Pretorius, targets T’Challa after learning of his attack on Percy Boraine.

83.text: Magneto -- Grey King of the Hellfire Club! But Sebastian Shaw smacks this usurper down!

86.text: Before X-Factor makes their way to Washington, they attend the funeral of Madelyne Prior. En route to Washington, X-Factor is attacked by Nanny and the Orphanmaker. Can they get the children to the Freedom Force in time?

90.text: It's Madripoor War Hulk when Joe Fixit comes to town! He's not sure who the players are yet - but Wolverine's decided who HE'S going to play with!

93.text: In part three of the 'Vision Quest Saga', the team must reconcile with a newly constructed Vision. Will Scarlet Witch find the automaton she loves in Vision 2.0?

94.text: Who does the world call on in the wake of super hero disasters? Meet the Clean-Up Op that handles the messes no one else wants to touch! Where there’s property damage…there’s Damage Control! Creator Dwayne McDuffie introduces you to the cast of characters responsible for keeping the Marvel Universe clean. It all starts here!

95.text: Will Namor claim the Invisible Girl for himself? Not if Reed Richards, Mister Fantastic, has his say!

97.text: The Sensational She-Hulk shows off her brute strength until she is hyponotized by the Ringmaster! Why does something always have to go wrong at the circus…

98.text: The government is about to be betrayed and overthrown! The Morituri are all either dead, in prison, or working for the enemy! Who remains that can save mankind? The answer is a shocker!

99.text: The tension on the front line can cause anything to happen…and in "Bunker" that’s exactly what goes down!
